1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:08,760
=Episode 21=

14
00:01:09,687 --> 00:01:11,157
(IP Trace Report)

15
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:21,700
Beiyan, you wanted to see me?

16
00:01:23,339 --> 00:01:24,340
Zichen.

17
00:01:24,540 --> 00:01:26,019
Why did you skip

18
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:27,179
the board meeting earlier?

19
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:28,459
Well.

20
00:01:30,779 --> 00:01:33,418
I just thought I should
meet with a few more investors.

21
00:01:33,419 --> 00:01:35,099
You know, more options
mean more open doors.

22
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:36,659
I saw how stressed you've been lately,

23
00:01:36,660 --> 00:01:38,060
so I wanted to help.

24
00:01:41,580 --> 00:01:44,860
You need to be careful
with choosing investors.

25
00:01:45,779 --> 00:01:49,340
Pick the wrong road,
and there's no turning back.

26
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:51,980
I get it.

27
00:01:52,259 --> 00:01:53,179
I really do.

28
00:01:59,339 --> 00:02:00,778
I heard that you've been

29
00:02:00,779 --> 00:02:02,179
getting pretty close to Ye Xin.

30
00:02:05,940 --> 00:02:08,340
Well, she's our partner.

31
00:02:08,340 --> 00:02:10,459
I'm still figuring out
how things work around the company.

32
00:02:10,460 --> 00:02:12,740
I need to learn the ropes, you know.

33
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:18,500
Zichen.

34
00:02:20,860 --> 00:02:22,139
As a Huo,

35
00:02:22,779 --> 00:02:24,058
your loyalty

36
00:02:24,059 --> 00:02:25,819
must always lie with the family.

37
00:02:29,099 --> 00:02:30,259
Of course.

38
00:02:34,339 --> 00:02:35,139
Beiyan,

39
00:02:35,379 --> 00:02:38,379
you must've been under a ton of pressure
at the board meeting earlier.

40
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:40,539
Doesn't matter.

41
00:02:40,980 --> 00:02:42,419
From now on, my main focus

42
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:44,539
will be the wedding.

43
00:03:01,659 --> 00:03:03,778
I've put all board business on hold.

44
00:03:03,779 --> 00:03:04,778
Moving forward,

45
00:03:04,779 --> 00:03:06,058
planning the wedding

46
00:03:06,059 --> 00:03:07,500
is my only priority.

47
00:03:09,700 --> 00:03:10,498
I get it now.

48
00:03:10,499 --> 00:03:11,739
You're throwing

49
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:13,379
a smokescreen.

50
00:03:13,539 --> 00:03:14,259
You need

51
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:15,378
to play the part of a CEO

52
00:03:15,379 --> 00:03:17,098
who's totally blinded by love

53
00:03:17,099 --> 00:03:17,658
and completely

54
00:03:17,659 --> 00:03:19,900
incapable of making
any rational decisions

55
00:03:20,180 --> 00:03:22,099
to catch them off guard.

56
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:23,659
Smart.

57
00:03:24,219 --> 00:03:24,699
However,

58
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:27,180
the whole "blinded by love" part

59
00:03:27,219 --> 00:03:28,259
isn't an act.

60
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:34,539
Come on.

61
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:35,539
Help me pick.

62
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,340
The wedding invitations.

63
00:03:37,619 --> 00:03:38,819
See which one you like.

64
00:03:39,819 --> 00:03:40,739
Why don't you decide?

65
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:42,780
They all look the same to me.

66
00:03:43,059 --> 00:03:45,618
Come on,
at least show a little interest.

67
00:03:45,619 --> 00:03:46,620
I am interested.

68
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,819
Let's go with this. This one looks great.

69
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:51,379
You're not even trying.

70
00:03:51,499 --> 00:03:53,859
It's like I'm the bride here.

71
00:03:55,659 --> 00:03:58,218
When a STEM girl
hits a project deadline,

72
00:03:58,219 --> 00:03:59,979
you'll just have to deal with it.

73
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:04,019
But have you found the point person

74
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:05,019
for the wedding?

75
00:04:05,020 --> 00:04:06,299
Knowing you,

76
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:07,419
at a time like this,

77
00:04:07,420 --> 00:04:08,058
I bet

78
00:04:08,059 --> 00:04:10,139
you've already
got eyes and ears around us.

79
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:13,019
Don't worry. It's taken care of.

80
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:14,300
They're all people I trust.

81
00:04:15,659 --> 00:04:16,780
What about the wedding dress?

82
00:04:16,820 --> 00:04:18,059
Which one's better?

83
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:20,340
I designed all of these myself.

84
00:04:23,219 --> 00:04:24,418
Aren't these dresses

85
00:04:24,419 --> 00:04:26,298
a bit too out there?

86
00:04:26,299 --> 00:04:27,778
Let's just leave the professional stuff

87
00:04:27,779 --> 00:04:29,340
to the actual professionals.

88
00:04:30,460 --> 00:04:31,539
Look at you.

89
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:33,780
Guess you do have
some standards after all.

90
00:04:35,020 --> 00:04:37,619
I just don't want
anything too ridiculous.

91
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,340
Then what kind do you actually like?

92
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:42,900
I'll choose.

93
00:04:46,739 --> 00:04:47,658
Actually,

94
00:04:47,659 --> 00:04:48,699
why don't we save this

95
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,418
for when we're
planning the real wedding?

96
00:04:50,419 --> 00:04:51,939
I think
the most important thing right now

97
00:04:51,940 --> 00:04:53,340
is focusing on the...

98
00:04:54,179 --> 00:04:56,259
Don't worry. I won't lose.

99
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:57,298
So you can

100
00:04:57,299 --> 00:04:59,780
afford to look a little further ahead.

101
00:05:01,219 --> 00:05:03,099
Wow, Huo Beiyan.

102
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:04,459
Pretending to catch me up on things

103
00:05:04,460 --> 00:05:06,260
when you're actually just hitting on me.

104
00:05:10,020 --> 00:05:11,340
Fine, I'll pick.

105
00:05:12,460 --> 00:05:13,499
If I'm picking the dress,

106
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,220
you're setting the venue, okay?

107
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:16,619
I already picked it out.

108
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,299
The Swiss Alps.

109
00:05:22,362 --> 00:05:28,145
♪You walked in
like you were still there♪

110
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:34,380
It's already so late.

111
00:05:34,659 --> 00:05:35,939
Why isn't he here yet?

112
00:05:35,940 --> 00:05:36,858
Has anyone called him?

113
00:05:36,859 --> 00:05:38,780
- He has zero sense of time.
- Seriously.

114
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:42,619
Sorry about that. I'm late.

115
00:05:50,859 --> 00:05:51,619
Everyone,

116
00:05:51,620 --> 00:05:53,460
I have a major announcement to make.

117
00:05:55,940 --> 00:05:56,900
What?

118
00:05:57,219 --> 00:05:58,499
Finally come to your senses?

119
00:05:59,539 --> 00:06:00,859
For the next ten days,

120
00:06:00,979 --> 00:06:02,139
all corporate matters

121
00:06:02,140 --> 00:06:03,978
will be handled by my cousin,

122
00:06:03,979 --> 00:06:05,580
Huo Zichen.

123
00:06:05,739 --> 00:06:06,459
As for me,

124
00:06:06,460 --> 00:06:07,579
I'll be putting all my energy

125
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,178
into planning the wedding for my wife,

126
00:06:09,179 --> 00:06:10,940
Xu Nange, and myself.

127
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,899
How can you be thinking

128
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:14,418
about a wedding at a time like this?

129
00:06:14,419 --> 00:06:15,538
This is nonsense.

130
00:06:15,539 --> 00:06:17,460
What kind of spell
did Xu Nange put you under?

131
00:06:18,099 --> 00:06:19,859
Happy wife, happy life.

132
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:22,140
And I'm sure

133
00:06:22,779 --> 00:06:23,778
the company will run just fine

134
00:06:23,779 --> 00:06:25,298
even without me around.

135
00:06:25,299 --> 00:06:26,140
Right?

136
00:06:26,339 --> 00:06:27,380
What? That's...

137
00:06:29,099 --> 00:06:30,738
- Beiyan,
- Is this some kind of joke?

138
00:06:30,739 --> 00:06:32,379
you're planning the wedding by yourself?

139
00:06:32,380 --> 00:06:34,020
Nange isn't even here.

140
00:06:35,299 --> 00:06:36,260
Don't worry.

141
00:06:36,620 --> 00:06:37,418
When the day comes,

142
00:06:37,419 --> 00:06:38,739
she'll show up.

143
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:45,778
(Beiyan,)

144
00:06:45,779 --> 00:06:46,699
(the experiment is now)

145
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:48,379
(at the final stage of data validation.)

146
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:49,859
(Everything is going smoothly.)

147
00:06:50,419 --> 00:06:51,700
(Got it.)

148
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,580
Meeting adjourned.

149
00:06:58,150 --> 00:06:59,019
You're leaving already?

150
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:00,899
- Mr. Huo.
- Mr. Huo?

151
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:02,538
This is an absolute joke.

152
00:07:02,539 --> 00:07:03,460
What...

153
00:07:11,779 --> 00:07:12,218
Come on.

154
00:07:12,219 --> 00:07:13,298
Let's get moving, everyone.

155
00:07:13,299 --> 00:07:14,019
Help me shift

156
00:07:14,020 --> 00:07:15,099
that flower basket.

157
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,539
Move these flowers over a bit.

158
00:07:17,260 --> 00:07:18,179
Keep an eye on this.

159
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:19,699
These tables have to be

160
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:20,600
perfectly lined up.

161
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,360
And the flowers over here.
Straighten them out.

162
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,820
- Keep them in a neat row.
- Got it.

163
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:24,699
Alright.

164
00:07:24,700 --> 00:07:26,259
Listen up while you work, everyone.

165
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:28,459
Today is Mr. Huo's wedding day.

166
00:07:28,460 --> 00:07:29,059
And for us

167
00:07:29,060 --> 00:07:30,019
at Huo Group,

168
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:31,379
it's the biggest event of the year.

169
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:32,858
So let's give it everything we've got.

170
00:07:32,859 --> 00:07:35,218
If we pull this off,
I'll personally hand out bonuses

171
00:07:35,219 --> 00:07:35,699
to everyone,

172
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:36,379
okay?

173
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:37,139
Okay!

174
00:07:37,140 --> 00:07:38,019
Do your best.

175
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:39,098
Mr. Shen,

176
00:07:39,099 --> 00:07:40,178
sorry I'm late.

177
00:07:40,179 --> 00:07:40,778
No worries.

178
00:07:40,779 --> 00:07:41,379
Professor Liang,

179
00:07:41,380 --> 00:07:42,538
how's your officiant speech

180
00:07:42,539 --> 00:07:43,820
coming along?

181
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:45,459
Mr. Shen,

182
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:47,338
if you asked me to give
an academic presentation,

183
00:07:47,339 --> 00:07:49,459
I wouldn't be sweating it at all.

184
00:07:49,460 --> 00:07:52,259
But being a wedding officiant
is a total first for me.

185
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:54,139
Plus, I can never remember lines.

186
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,538
Don't be nervous, Professor Liang.

187
00:07:55,539 --> 00:07:57,178
Your star student is marrying my boss.

188
00:07:57,179 --> 00:07:58,338
This is cause for celebration.

189
00:07:58,339 --> 00:07:58,778
Look.

190
00:07:58,779 --> 00:08:00,859
You'll never have to worry
about research funding.

191
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:02,218
That's exactly

192
00:08:02,219 --> 00:08:03,619
why I'm so nervous.

193
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:06,260
If I mess up my speech on stage,

194
00:08:06,339 --> 00:08:08,820
it's going to be a disaster.

195
00:08:09,460 --> 00:08:10,460
I mean, look.

196
00:08:10,739 --> 00:08:11,738
The...

197
00:08:11,739 --> 00:08:13,380
The wedding is about to start,

198
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,099
and I haven't prepared a single thing.

199
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:17,460
Don't worry.

200
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:17,978
I know

201
00:08:17,979 --> 00:08:19,858
it's your first time
doing something like this.

202
00:08:19,859 --> 00:08:20,499
So

203
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,140
I wrote a script for you.

204
00:08:22,620 --> 00:08:23,858
You're a lifesaver, Mr. Shen.

205
00:08:23,859 --> 00:08:25,858
I'm sure whatever you wrote is perfect.

206
00:08:25,859 --> 00:08:27,940
Here, go ahead and look it over.

207
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:29,298
Alright.

208
00:08:29,299 --> 00:08:30,659
Let me see.

209
00:08:43,980 --> 00:08:45,019
Look, Mr. Huo.

210
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,979
This dress is straight off
the Paris runway.

211
00:08:46,980 --> 00:08:48,880
The design concept
is rooted in natural aesthetics.

212
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:51,320
It features a structured,
tailored bodice with a skirt designed to...

213
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:51,899
Too cliche.

214
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:52,660
Next one.

215
00:08:52,779 --> 00:08:53,619
This piece features

216
00:08:53,620 --> 00:08:55,379
a unique texture woven
from Italian silk organza

217
00:08:55,380 --> 00:08:56,578
and French duchess satin.

218
00:08:56,579 --> 00:08:58,298
The skirt unfolds like a blossom,

219
00:08:58,299 --> 00:08:59,058
layer by layer.

220
00:08:59,059 --> 00:08:59,698
Next.

221
00:08:59,699 --> 00:09:00,820
This isn't dramatic enough.

222
00:09:02,539 --> 00:09:04,298
The inspiration for this dress

223
00:09:04,299 --> 00:09:07,099
comes from the transition
of polar day and night in Antarctica.

224
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:08,820
- The shoulders feature...
- Next.

225
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:11,339
What about this one, Mr. Huo?

226
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:12,979
This is our...

227
00:09:25,059 --> 00:09:25,979
Uncle Beixiang,

228
00:09:26,380 --> 00:09:27,259
why are you

229
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:28,619
writing this yourself?

230
00:09:28,819 --> 00:09:30,339
You don't get it.

231
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:31,979
It's been ages since our family

232
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:33,379
had something this big to celebrate.

233
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:36,298
We should take this chance
to make sure everyone has a great time

234
00:09:36,299 --> 00:09:37,420
and enjoys themselves.

235
00:09:37,939 --> 00:09:38,698
Uncle Beixiang,

236
00:09:38,699 --> 00:09:40,899
Beiyan never said
he'd be coming home after the wedding.

237
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,859
And we don't have
a traditional bridal procession.

238
00:09:43,699 --> 00:09:46,139
That's for me to worry about.

239
00:09:46,140 --> 00:09:47,379
Just leave it to me.

240
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:48,499
Alright, Uncle Beixiang.

241
00:09:48,579 --> 00:09:49,538
Save the lecture.

242
00:09:49,539 --> 00:09:50,899
I'll get to work.

243
00:09:51,860 --> 00:09:53,580
What are you rushing off to do?

244
00:09:53,620 --> 00:09:54,778
Listen up.

245
00:09:54,779 --> 00:09:57,099
The most important thing for us now

246
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:59,060
is Beiyan's wedding.

247
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,818
Get over to his room

248
00:10:00,819 --> 00:10:02,259
and help set things up.

249
00:10:02,659 --> 00:10:03,379
Later,

250
00:10:03,380 --> 00:10:04,698
wheel your grandma over there too.

251
00:10:04,699 --> 00:10:06,859
Let her get a taste
of the festive spirit.

252
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:08,379
Got it, Uncle Beixiang.

253
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:09,259
Off you go.

254
00:10:11,299 --> 00:10:12,658
What should I write?

255
00:10:12,659 --> 00:10:14,700
Soaring together
through life's open sky.

256
00:10:14,819 --> 00:10:17,259
Bound in a love that time cannot untie.

257
00:10:25,299 --> 00:10:26,979
(Xu Nange,)

258
00:10:27,620 --> 00:10:29,820
(where on earth are you?)

259
00:10:36,437 --> 00:10:38,182
(Ye Xin)

260
00:10:39,539 --> 00:10:40,259
Hello?

261
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:42,099
Did you find what we were looking for?

262
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:44,499
Huo Beiyan is taking his sweet time,

263
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,339
even making a trip
to pick out wedding dresses.

264
00:10:46,340 --> 00:10:48,418
We're running out of time here.

265
00:10:48,419 --> 00:10:49,938
Where exactly is Xu Nange hiding?

266
00:10:49,939 --> 00:10:51,739
What on earth is Huo Beiyan plotting?

267
00:10:51,740 --> 00:10:53,578
You need to find a lead.

268
00:10:53,579 --> 00:10:54,660
I know.

269
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:56,698
Everything is moving forward as planned.

270
00:10:56,699 --> 00:10:57,859
Don't worry.

271
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,379
Xu Nange won't get in our way.

272
00:11:00,380 --> 00:11:01,578
Huo Zichen,

273
00:11:01,579 --> 00:11:03,698
once Xu Nange shows herself,

274
00:11:03,699 --> 00:11:06,099
we won't have much room left
to make our move.

275
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:09,099
You wouldn't want Beiyan
to walk away with the girl

276
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:11,180
and keep a tight grip
on Huo Group, would you?

277
00:11:12,299 --> 00:11:13,499
Stop poking at my sore spots.

278
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:15,019
I want this way more than you.

279
00:11:18,179 --> 00:11:19,340
Don't worry.

280
00:11:19,459 --> 00:11:20,739
